ks, chamber music, concertos, and jazz. Her choices include composers such as Bach, Mozart, Beethoven, Robert Schumann, Tchaikovsky, Debussy, Gershwin, and Philip Glass. Looking at this history from a modern performer’s perspective, she acknowledges neglected women composers and players including Fanny Mendelssohn, Maria Szymanowska, Clara Schumann, and Amy Beach.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Sep 2021) 0aPiano musicxHistory and criticism. 0aPianoxHistory. 7aMUSIC / Musical Instruments / Piano & Keyboard.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300262865423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300262865/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles